---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="PlainHazard privacy policy. Learn how we handle your data and protect your privacy."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-8 md:py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Last updated: March 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-6 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        PlainHazard does not require user registration or collect personal information directly. We use third-party analytics and advertising services that may collect certain data as described below.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We use privacy-focused analytics (Umami) to understand how visitors use our site. This service collects anonymized usage data including page views, referrer information, and general device information. No personally identifiable information is collected or stored.
      </p>
      <p>
        We also use Google Analytics 4 (GA4) which may collect additional data subject to Google's privacy policy.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Advertising</h2>
      <p>
        We use Google AdSense to display advertisements. Google may use cookies and similar technologies to serve ads based on your browsing history. You can manage your ad preferences through <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand-600 hover:underline dark:text-brand-400">Google's Ad Settings</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        This site uses cookies for analytics, advertising, and user preferences (such as dark mode). You can control cookie settings through your browser. EU visitors will see a consent dialog before non-essential cookies are activated.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Third-Party Services</h2>
      <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-1">
        <li>Google Analytics 4 — <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand-600 hover:underline dark:text-brand-400">Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li>Google AdSense — <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand-600 hover:underline dark:text-brand-400">Ad Policies</a></li>
        <li>Cloudflare — <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand-600 hover:underline dark:text-brand-400">Privacy Policy</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">California Residents (CCPA)</h2>
      <p>
        California residents have the right to know what personal information is collected and to request its deletion. As we collect minimal data, there is generally no personal information to delete. You may opt out of personalized advertising through <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand-600 hover:underline dark:text-brand-400">Google's Ad Settings</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
